<doc id="746928" wikidata="Q5511602" url="?curid=746928" title="Félix Lavilla">
<text>Félix Lavilla Muñarriz (11 June 1928, Pamplona – 14 January 2013 Madrid) was a Spanish pianist, composer and a well-known accompanist, son of a music teacher and band master of the municipal band of Errenteria in Gipuzkoa, Basque Autonomous Community. He was perhaps best known for his collaborations with the mezzo-soprano Teresa Berganza, to whom he was married from 1957 to 1977. The couple regularly recorded and gave recitals together.

