<doc id="747100" wikidata="Q3401778" url="?curid=747100" title="Olympiada, Kozani">
<text>Olympiada (), known before 1927 as Rakita (), is a village and a community of the Eordaia municipality. Before the 2011 local government reform it was part of the municipality of Ptolemaida, of which it was a municipal district. The 2021 census recorded 537 inhabitants in the village.

==History==
Olympiada was first mentioned in an Ottoman defter of 1481, the village, then known as &quot;Rakita&quot;, had forty-five households and produced vines, honey, and swine.

